Face mask is important for skin care treatment.A good face mask can leave your face cleansed and smooth and makes your face relaxed and rejuvenated.
Face masks help to cleanse impurities from the skin like oils, dirt and makeup. It helps to open the pores and deep cleanse the impurities that cause infections and pimples.
A good face mask helps to circulate the blood. When the mask hardens on the face, there is a sensation that drives the blood vessels to expand and then improves the skin tone. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-660203 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ebony-957x598.jpg" alt="" width="957" height="598" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ebony-957x598.jpg 957w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ebony-487x304.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ebony-974x609.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ebony-320x200.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ebony-640x400.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ebony-600x375.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ebony.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 957px) 100vw, 957px" /> There are so many brands of face masks that you can buy from supermarkets or beauty stores. But there are natural face masks that you can mix in your kitchen which can give an amazing result. You can absolutely do this yourself. Honey Oats Face Masks To make Honey Oats Face Masks, you need;
Ground oats,
Coconut oil and
Natural Honey.
Mix the ingredients together and you will have a paste.
Apply on the face and leave for 15 minutes and wash. Papaya Face Mask To make papaya face mask, you need 1 Papaya [Pawpaw]
1 tbsp, NaturalÂ  Honey
1 egg white Mix the Papaya, honey and the egg white. Whisk the egg before you add. Mix thoroughly and apply on the face. Leave on the face for 15 minutes and wash off.
do this at least 2 or 3 times a week for a clearer, even skin tone.